00:25:42.068 --> 00:25:43.484
Christina: One of my
all time favorite books

00:25:43.484 --> 00:25:45.651
is Neal Stephenson's The Diamond Age

00:25:45.651 --> 00:25:48.099
and in it he's got the Young
Lady's Illustrated Primer

00:25:48.099 --> 00:25:50.317
and this rich guy builds this
book so his granddaughter

00:25:50.317 --> 00:25:53.369
can have this tremendous education
and one of the aspects of it

00:25:53.369 --> 00:25:56.203
is that all the content and the
learning materials are in there,

00:25:56.203 --> 00:25:59.895
but there are these ractors
who are people who are tracking

00:25:59.895 --> 00:26:01.811
and watching as they
move through the book,

00:26:01.811 --> 00:26:04.917
they actually have a dashboard
with metrics in the book.

00:26:04.917 --> 00:26:08.218
I'm thinking about our social
network and your materials,

00:26:08.218 --> 00:26:10.043
whether it's e-books or videos,

00:26:10.043 --> 00:26:12.855
and wondering if we could
create Khan ractors,

00:26:12.855 --> 00:26:15.493
who would be indexed, either
the videos or materials,

00:26:15.493 --> 00:26:18.043
and they would be people who
were certified and volunteered

00:26:18.043 --> 00:26:19.862
so that the kid at any point
where they're stumbling

00:26:19.862 --> 00:26:23.127
could maybe hit a button,
get an IM, start to engage

00:26:23.127 --> 00:26:26.460
with that community to get that kind
of personalized stuff worldwide.

00:26:26.460 --> 00:26:28.460
Sal: Yeah, that's exactly -

00:26:28.460 --> 00:26:30.210
We have to figure out the
details of how we implement that,

00:26:30.210 --> 00:26:32.993
but that's our next level,
because the first level is videos,

00:26:32.993 --> 00:26:35.780
the second level are these
exercises and dashboard,

00:26:35.780 --> 00:26:37.158
the next level's the community.

00:26:37.158 --> 00:26:39.411
We're pushing two million
unique users a month

00:26:39.411 --> 00:26:43.410
and that's enough, that's
critical mass, that's growing.

00:26:43.410 --> 00:26:44.485
There's a couple things.

00:26:44.485 --> 00:26:48.028
One is just the model of
volunteerism, peer-to-peer,

00:26:48.028 --> 00:26:51.060
"Hey, I'm at my desk, I have an hour
