00:26:56.578 --> 00:26:58.243
based on what they know
and what they don't know.

00:26:58.243 --> 00:26:59.708
And get the kids tutoring.

00:26:59.708 --> 00:27:02.704
It's either that model or
we're thinking of having

00:27:02.704 --> 00:27:05.078
some kind of a perpetual office hours.

00:27:05.078 --> 00:27:07.709
Volunteers could say, "Hey,
I'll be free at this time.

00:27:07.709 --> 00:27:11.214
"I'm in Malaysia and I'll
be free from 2:00 to 3:00 PM

00:27:11.214 --> 00:27:13.076
"and I know these set of topics."

00:27:13.076 --> 00:27:14.785
If we get a critical mass,
and you actually don't need

00:27:14.785 --> 00:27:16.887
that many people, but if
you get enough people,

00:27:16.887 --> 00:27:19.357
you could have exactly what you
said as soon as you're stuck.

00:27:19.357 --> 00:27:20.991
It's not even something
that has to be scheduled.

00:27:20.991 --> 00:27:23.225
As soon as you're stuck,
you say, "I need help,"

00:27:23.225 --> 00:27:25.864
and it immediately points you.

00:27:25.864 --> 00:27:29.632
I'm actually on page 85
of Diamond Age right now,

00:27:29.632 --> 00:27:31.493
so I haven't gotten to the ractor part.

00:27:31.493 --> 00:27:33.243
(unintelligible) Oh, is it?

00:27:33.243 --> 00:27:35.873
Yeah, but we're clearly
reading the same books,

00:27:35.873 --> 00:27:39.277
but yes, that's where -

00:27:39.277 --> 00:27:43.713
It's funny, each layer, we actually
think that's going to be the big play,

00:27:43.713 --> 00:27:45.578
not what we've already done.

00:27:45.578 --> 00:27:48.828
Jeff: Would love to throw it
out there as a Hackday challenge

00:27:48.828 --> 00:27:50.744
for those of you in the room or watching.

00:27:50.744 --> 00:27:53.243
It'd be pretty cool to
do something very similar

00:27:53.243 --> 00:27:57.194
and I had a similar idea based
on originally hearing you speak.

00:27:57.194 --> 00:27:59.411
With 100 million members, professionals

00:27:59.411 --> 00:28:03.136
with the right kind of
skills and backgrounds,

00:28:03.136 --> 00:28:07.103
one of the things that
was most exciting to me

00:28:07.103 --> 00:28:10.742
was that anyone can come
online to lend a hand

00:28:10.742 --> 00:28:13.328
and help mentor and answer questions.

00:28:13.328 --> 00:28:15.611
I think it would be a very
cool hack to figure out a way

00:28:15.611 --> 00:28:17.546
to do exactly what Christina
was just suggesting.

00:28:17.546 --> 00:28:21.076
Click a button and we could
pair up the right kids

00:28:21.076 --> 00:28:24.660
with the right mentors from among
our professional membership.

00:28:24.660 --> 00:28:27.560
The other idea that's probably
a little more in depth

00:28:27.560 --> 00:28:32.666
than a hack is to start to
leverage everything you've done

00:28:32.666 --> 00:28:35.878
for the kids for vocational training

00:28:35.878 --> 00:28:40.334
because one of the things
we all hear increasingly

00:28:40.334 --> 00:28:43.547
is that it's not that there's
not jobs available at times

00:28:43.547 --> 00:28:45.000
or in certain geographies.

00:28:45.000 --> 00:28:46.834
There are jobs available, it's
just that people don't have

00:28:46.834 --> 00:28:49.085
the skills to take advantage of them.

00:28:49.085 --> 00:28:52.960
If we could somehow
re-skin some of the backend

00:28:52.960 --> 00:28:56.585
and add vocational training modules

00:28:56.585 --> 00:28:59.066
and then again, partner up
the people that need to learn

00:28:59.066 --> 00:29:02.416
with the professional membership,
we could really do some good.

00:29:02.416 --> 00:29:05.418
Sal: Yeah, absolutely.

00:29:05.418 --> 00:29:07.473
Especially with the ...

00:29:07.473 --> 00:29:10.611
Yeah, that's a way to donate your time.

00:29:10.611 --> 00:29:13.929
There could even be some
badging that transcends

00:29:13.929 --> 00:29:16.028
what you all are doing
